# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

Manages a [Temporal Schedule](https://docs.temporal.io/workflows#schedule). Schedules trigger workflow executions on a defined cadence using cron expressions, calendar specs, or fixed intervals.

## Example Usage

### Cron-based schedule

```terraform
resource "temporalschedules_schedule" "daily_report" {
  namespace = "default"
  address   = "temporal.example.com:7233"
  api_key   = var.temporal_api_key
  name      = "daily-report"

  action {
    workflow_type = "ReportWorkflow"
    task_queue    = "report-queue"
    input_payload = jsonencode({ format = "pdf" })
  }

  spec {
    cron_expressions = ["0 9 * * *"]
    timezone         = "America/New_York"
  }
}
```

### Calendar-based schedule

```terraform
resource "temporalschedules_schedule" "weekday_job" {
  namespace = "default"
  address   = "temporal.example.com:7233"
  name      = "weekday-job"

  action {
    workflow_type = "ProcessWorkflow"
    task_queue    = "processing-queue"
  }

  spec {
    timezone = "America/New_York"

    calendar {
      hour        = "9"
      minute      = "0"
      day_of_week = "1-5"
      comment     = "Weekday mornings"
    }
  }
}
```

### Interval-based schedule

```terraform
resource "temporalschedules_schedule" "health_check" {
  namespace = "default"
  address   = "temporal.example.com:7233"
  name      = "health-check"

  action {
    workflow_type = "HealthCheckWorkflow"
    task_queue    = "monitoring-queue"
  }

  spec {
    interval {
      every  = "4h"
      offset = "5m"
    }

    jitter = "30s"
  }
}
```

